        {"name":"Anchor & Tide Seafood","price":42,"rating":4.7,"cuisine":"Seafood","tip":"Arrive before 6 PM to snag a window seat overlooking the bay.","desc":"A beloved waterfront institution serving Dungeness crab and clam chowder with stunning views of the Golden Gate.","photo":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8f/Buffet_at_Hotel_Sisimiut.jpg/960px-Buffet_at_Hotel_Sisimiut.jpg"},
        {"name":"Fog Harbor Fish House","price":38,"rating":4.5,"cuisine":"Seafood","tip":"Order the cioppino — it feeds two and is worth every penny.","desc":"A Fisherman's Wharf classic that sources its catch daily and pairs it with locally crafted sourdough bread.","photo":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/4e/Dinner_02_11_2019_Mussels%2C_Calimari%2C_Prawns_%26_Chorizo_in_a_spicy_tomato_sauce_on_Linguine_with_parmesan._%2849007855028%29.jpg/960px-Dinner_02_11_2019_Mussels%2C_Calimari%2C_Prawns_%26_Chorizo_in_a_spicy_tomato_sauce_on_Linguine_with_parmesan._%2849007855028%29.jpg"},
        {"name":"Swan Oyster Depot","price":35,"rating":4.8,"cuisine":"Seafood","tip":"Arrive by 8 AM — the line forms fast and they often sell out by early afternoon.","desc":"A standing-room-only counter diner open since 1912, renowned for its pristine raw oysters and shrimp Louie.","photo":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-k1dGnJYZzI0?w=800&auto=format&fit=crop&q=80"},
        {"name":"Pacific Catch","price":22,"rating":4.3,"cuisine":"Seafood","tip":"The fish tacos are the standout — mix and match with the mango habanero salsa.","desc":"A casual West Coast fish house bringing global flavors to sustainable local seafood in a lively neighborhood setting.","photo":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/4e/Dinner_02_11_2019_Mussels%2C_Calimari%2C_Prawns_%26_Chorizo_in_a_spicy_tomato_sauce_on_Linguine_with_parmesan._%2849007855028%29.jpg/960px-Dinner_02_11_2019_Mussels%2C_Calimari%2C_Prawns_%26_Chorizo_in_a_spicy_tomato_sauce_on_Linguine_with_parmesan._%2849007855028%29.jpg"},
        {"name":"Waterbar","price":55,"rating":4.6,"cuisine":"Seafood","tip":"Book the outdoor patio table for an unobstructed view of the Bay Bridge at sunset.","desc":"An upscale Embarcadero restaurant featuring a dramatic two-story aquarium, raw bar, and refined California seafood plates.","photo":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/4e/Dinner_02_11_2019_Mussels%2C_Calimari%2C_Prawns_%26_Chorizo_in_a_spicy_tomato_sauce_on_Linguine_with_parmesan._%2849007855028%29.jpg/960px-Dinner_02_11_2019_Mussels%2C_Calimari%2C_Prawns_%26_Chorizo_in_a_spicy_tomato_sauce_on_Linguine_with_parmesan._%2849007855028%29.jpg"},
        {"name":"Scoma's of San Francisco","price":48,"rating":4.4,"cuisine":"Seafood","tip":"Ask your server about the catch of the day — it's almost always the freshest thing on the menu.","desc":"A historic pier-side institution where local fishermen once traded their catch for hot meals since 1965.","photo":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/80/Airline_meal_asiana.jpg/960px-Airline_meal_asiana.jpg"},
        {"name":"The Crab Station","price":28,"rating":4.2,"cuisine":"Seafood","tip":"Grab extra napkins — the garlic butter whole crab is deliciously messy.","desc":"A no-frills wharf stall beloved by locals for heaping portions of cracked Dungeness crab at fair prices.","photo":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/b4/Food_Series_%28Home-made%29_of_Mooncake_%28Mid-autumn%29_Festival_-_4th_Crabs_Dish_wanted_to_join.jpg/960px-Food_Series_%28Home-made%29_of_Mooncake_%28Mid-autumn%29_Festival_-_4th_Crabs_Dish_wanted_to_join.jpg"},
        {"name":"Hog Island Oyster Co.","price":45,"rating":4.7,"cuisine":"Seafood","tip":"Happy hour on weekdays offers a dozen oysters at half price — plan accordingly.","desc":"Farm-to-table oyster bar at the Ferry Building sourcing directly from their Tomales Bay shellfish farm.","photo":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/80/Airline_meal_asiana.jpg/960px-Airline_meal_asiana.jpg"},
        {"name":"PPQ Dungeness Island","price":30,"rating":4.5,"cuisine":"Seafood","tip":"The garlic noodles are a must-order side that regulars swear by.","desc":"A Richmond District favorite blending Vietnamese technique with San Francisco's prized Dungeness crab in roasted and cracked preparations.","photo":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/ba/Garnelen_in_Toast_3.jpg/960px-Garnelen_in_Toast_3.jpg"},
        {"name":"Tartine Bakery","price":14,"rating":4.8,"cuisine":"Bakery","tip":"Country loaves come out around 5 PM — join the queue at 4:30 to guarantee one.","desc":"The Mission's most celebrated bakery, famous for naturally leavened country bread with a crackling crust and custardy crumb.","photo":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/0/0e/Belgium_2013_%2811620905224%29.jpg/800px-Belgium_2013_%2811620905224%29.jpg"},
        {"name":"Acme Bread Company","price":9,"rating":4.6,"cuisine":"Bakery","tip":"The pain au levain disappears fast — pick it up in the morning at the Ferry Building stall.","desc":"A Bay Area artisan institution that helped ignite the American sourdough revival with its hand-shaped European-style loaves.","photo":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/0/0e/Belgium_2013_%2811620905224%29.jpg/800px-Belgium_2013_%2811620905224%29.jpg"},
        {"name":"B. Patisserie","price":12,"rating":4.7,"cuisine":"Bakery","tip":"The kouign-amann is the signature — come early because it's gone by mid-morning most days.","desc":"A French-inspired patisserie on California Street turning out flawlessly laminated pastries and elegant tarts in a serene setting.","photo":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/0/0e/Belgium_2013_%2811620905224%29.jpg/800px-Belgium_2013_%2811620905224%29.jpg"},
        {"name":"Arizmendi Bakery","price":8,"rating":4.5,"cuisine":"Bakery","tip":"Check their online calendar to see which specialty pizza is available that day before you go.","desc":"A worker-owned cooperative bakery adored for its rotating sourdough pizzas, seeded breads, and community-focused ethos.","photo":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/0/0e/Belgium_2013_%2811620905224%29.jpg/800px-Belgium_2013_%2811620905224%29.jpg"},
        {"name":"La Boulangerie de San Francisco","price":11,"rating":4.4,"cuisine":"Bakery","tip":"The croque monsieur sandwich pairs perfectly with a café au lait on a foggy morning.","desc":"A neighborhood French bakery with buttery croissants, rustic baguettes, and café snacks that feel genuinely Parisian.","photo":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/0/0e/Belgium_2013_%2811620905224%29.jpg/800px-Belgium_2013_%2811620905224%29.jpg"},
        {"name":"Noe Valley Bakery","price":7,"rating":4.3,"cuisine":"Bakery","tip":"Their birthday cakes can be ordered a day in advance and are worth the planning.","desc":"A beloved neighborhood spot known for generous slices of cake, focaccia sandwiches, and unpretentious community warmth.","photo":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/0/0e/Belgium_2013_%2811620905224%29.jpg/800px-Belgium_2013_%2811620905224%29.jpg"},
        {"name":"Manresa Bread","price":13,"rating":4.7,"cuisine":"Bakery","tip":"The seeded rye batard makes an exceptional base for avocado toast at home.","desc":"An extension of the Michelin-starred Los Gatos restaurant, bringing refined grain sourcing and natural fermentation to everyday loaves.","photo":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/0/0e/Belgium_2013_%2811620905224%29.jpg/800px-Belgium_2013_%2811620905224%29.jpg"},
        {"name":"Thorough Bread and Pastry","price":10,"rating":4.4,"cuisine":"Bakery","tip":"The almond croissant is twice-baked and twice as rich — split it with a friend.","desc":"A Castro District gem run by a culinary school where talented students turn out impressive pastries and rustic loaves daily.","photo":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/0/0e/Belgium_2013_%2811620905224%29.jpg/800px-Belgium_2013_%2811620905224%29.jpg"},
        {"name":"The Mill","price":11,"rating":4.6,"cuisine":"Bakery","tip":"Pair their thick-cut toast with Four Barrel coffee for the quintessential SF breakfast experience.","desc":"A Divisadero hotspot collaborating with Josey Baker Bread to serve thick-sliced heritage-grain toast with curated seasonal toppings.","photo":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/0/0e/Belgium_2013_%2811620905224%29.jpg/800px-Belgium_2013_%2811620905224%29.jpg"},
        {"name":"Jane the Bakery","price":10,"rating":4.5,"cuisine":"Bakery","tip":"The egg sandwich on their house focaccia is a standout morning meal before exploring Golden Gate Park.","desc":"A bright, welcoming café and bakery known for high-quality pastries, sandwiches, and coffee sourced from local roasters.","photo":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/0/0e/Belgium_2013_%2811620905224%29.jpg/800px-Belgium_2013_%2811620905224%29.jpg"},
        {"name":"La Taqueria","price":13,"rating":4.8,"cuisine":"Mission Burrito","tip":"Order the carnitas burrito without rice — true Mission style packs more meat and flavor.","desc":"The definitive Mission burrito birthplace, famous for its precise construction, slow-cooked meats, and strictly no-filler philosophy since 1973.","photo":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/0/01/Empanada_flor_de_Calabaza.jpg/800px-Empanada_flor_de_Calabaza.jpg"},
        {"name":"El Farolito","price":11,"rating":4.7,"cuisine":"Mission Burrito","tip":"Go late-night on weekends when the post-bar crowd thins around 1 AM and the al pastor is freshest.","desc":"A Mission District institution open past midnight, slinging tightly wrapped super burritos to generations of devoted late-night fans.","photo":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/60/Burrito.JPG/800px-Burrito.JPG"},
        {"name":"Taqueria Cancun","price":10,"rating":4.5,"cuisine":"Mission Burrito","tip":"The carne asada super burrito with guacamole is worth the small upcharge every time.","desc":"A no-frills counter taqueria on Mission Street beloved by locals for generously sized burritos at honest prices.","photo":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/17/Shredded_pork_burrito.jpg/800px-Shredded_pork_burrito.jpg"},
        {"name":"Pancho Villa Taqueria","price":12,"rating":4.6,"cuisine":"Mission Burrito","tip":"The line moves quickly — study the menu board while you wait so you're ready to order.","desc":"A Mission staple with a vast menu of burritos, quesadillas, and tacos assembled fresh in an open kitchen.","photo":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/0/01/Empanada_flor_de_Calabaza.jpg/800px-Empanada_flor_de_Calabaza.jpg"},
        {"name":"Papalote Mexican Grill","price":13,"rating":4.6,"cuisine":"Mission Burrito","tip":"Their bottled salsa is sold at local shops — grab one to take home as a souvenir.","desc":"Famous for a cult-status roasted tomato salsa that inspired nationwide shipping demand and anchors every burrito order.","photo":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/0/01/Empanada_flor_de_Calabaza.jpg/800px-Empanada_flor_de_Calabaza.jpg"},
        {"name":"Taqueria El Buen Sabor","price":11,"rating":4.4,"cuisine":"Mission Burrito","tip":"Ask for the green tomatillo salsa — it's house-made and rarely makes it to the self-serve bar.","desc":"A neighborhood fixture dishing up hearty Mission burritos with freshly pressed tortillas and house-cooked beans.","photo":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/17/Shredded_pork_burrito.jpg/800px-Shredded_pork_burrito.jpg"},
        {"name":"Roosevelt Tamale Parlor","price":14,"rating":4.3,"cuisine":"Mission Burrito","tip":"The combo plate lets you sample tamales alongside a classic burrito — ideal for first-timers.","desc":"One of the oldest Mexican restaurants in the city, blending tamale traditions with Mission burrito culture since 1919.","photo":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/60/Burrito.JPG/800px-Burrito.JPG"},
        {"name":"Taqueria Vallarta","price":10,"rating":4.4,"cuisine":"Mission Burrito","tip":"The breakfast burrito with chorizo and egg is a powerful start to a full day of sightseeing.","desc":"A quick-service taqueria favored for its value-packed burritos and vibrant salsas across multiple Mission locations.","photo":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/0/01/Empanada_flor_de_Calabaza.jpg/800px-Empanada_flor_de_Calabaza.jpg"},
        {"name":"Taqueria Guadalajara","price":11,"rating":4.3,"cuisine":"Mission Burrito","tip":"Go for the pollo asado — it's marinated overnight and stands out from the standard chicken options.","desc":"A longstanding Mission eatery with a loyal following for its grilled meats, hearty bean burritos, and warm tortillas.","photo":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/60/Burrito.JPG/800px-Burrito.JPG"},
        {"name":"Gracias Madre","price":22,"rating":4.5,"cuisine":"Mission Burrito","tip":"The plantain and black bean burrito proves that plant-based Mission burritos can be just as satisfying.","desc":"A plant-based Mexican restaurant in the Mission that crafts soulful, organic burritos rooted in Mexican culinary tradition.","photo":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/0/01/Empanada_flor_de_Calabaza.jpg/800px-Empanada_flor_de_Calabaza.jpg"},
        {"name":"Zuni Café","price":52,"rating":4.7,"cuisine":"California Cuisine","tip":"The brick oven-roasted chicken for two must be ordered 45 minutes ahead — it's worth every second of the wait.","desc":"An iconic Hayes Valley landmark that helped define California cuisine through seasonal ingredients, wood-fired cooking, and timeless hospitality since 1979.","photo":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-rPg8P5pgHMQ?w=800&auto=format&fit=crop&q=80"},
        {"name":"Rich Table","price":60,"rating":4.8,"cuisine":"California Cuisine","tip":"The sardine chips are a famous bar snack — order them the moment you sit down.","desc":"A Hayes Valley restaurant from husband-and-wife chefs showcasing inventive California cooking with unexpected flavor combinations and farm sourcing.","photo":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/c0/Rich_Table_San_Francisco_-_Dec._2025.jpg/800px-Rich_Table_San_Francisco_-_Dec._2025.jpg"},
        {"name":"Nopa","price":45,"rating":4.7,"cuisine":"California Cuisine","tip":"Late-night dining until 1 AM makes this a perfect post-show destination without the usual reservation scramble.","desc":"A cavernous, convivial NoPa neighborhood restaurant celebrated for its wood-fired seasonal California dishes and lively communal energy.","photo":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e2/Tres_hombres_sentados_a_la_mesa%2C_by_Diego_Vel%C3%A1zquez.jpg/800px-Tres_hombres_sentados_a_la_mesa%2C_by_Diego_Vel%C3%A1zquez.jpg"},
        {"name":"State Bird Provisions","price":65,"rating":4.9,"cuisine":"California Cuisine","tip":"Snag a spot at the counter to watch the dim-sum-style cart service up close and pick freely.","desc":"A Michelin-starred Fillmore District restaurant serving California small plates dim-sum style from roving carts in a buzzy dining room.","photo":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/b4/Chez_Panisse_pizza.jpg/800px-Chez_Panisse_pizza.jpg"},
        {"name":"SPQR","price":55,"rating":4.6,"cuisine":"California Cuisine","tip":"The housemade pasta changes seasonally — let your server recommend the current standout before ordering.","desc":"A refined Fillmore restaurant weaving California produce into Italian-inspired pasta and cured-meat dishes in a sophisticated, intimate setting.","photo":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/b4/Chez_Panisse_pizza.jpg/800px-Chez_Panisse_pizza.jpg"},
        {"name":"Foreign Cinema","price":50,"rating":4.6,"cuisine":"California Cuisine","tip":"Request an outdoor patio table to dine beneath the projected film while enjoying the heated terrace.","desc":"A Mission restaurant and cultural venue projecting art-house films onto a courtyard wall while serving inspired California cuisine.","photo":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/b4/Chez_Panisse_pizza.jpg/800px-Chez_Panisse_pizza.jpg"},
        {"name":"Cotogna","price":58,"rating":4.7,"cuisine":"California Cuisine","tip":"The wood-fired seasonal vegetables are often more impressive than the proteins — don't overlook them.","desc":"A rustic Italian-Californian trattoria from chef Michael Tusk featuring house-milled pasta, fire-roasted meats, and market-driven antipasti.","photo":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/af/Red_and_white_wine_in_glass.jpg/800px-Red_and_white_wine_in_glass.jpg"},
        {"name":"The Progress","price":62,"rating":4.7,"cuisine":"California Cuisine","tip":"Order the communal family-style menu for the table — it's designed to be shared and showcases the kitchen's range.","desc":"Sister restaurant to State Bird Provisions, offering a more structured California feast format with equally inventive seasonal cooking.","photo":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/66/Kendall-Jackson_May_Farm-To-Table_Dinner_-_Stierch_08.jpg/800px-Kendall-Jackson_May_Farm-To-Table_Dinner_-_Stierch_08.jpg"},
        {"name":"Bellota","price":54,"rating":4.5,"cuisine":"California Cuisine","tip":"The Ibérico ham carving station is a showpiece — ask for a tasting portion to start your meal.","desc":"A SoMa restaurant merging California seasonal produce with Spanish influences and an impressive collection of Ibérico cured products.","photo":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/b4/Chez_Panisse_pizza.jpg/800px-Chez_Panisse_pizza.jpg"},
        {"name":"Chez Panisse Café-Style SF","price":48,"rating":4.6,"cuisine":"Cal-Med","tip":"Order the whole roasted fish if available — it captures the essence of Cal-Med cooking at its best.","desc":"Inspired by Alice Waters' legacy, this Cal-Med kitchen marries wood-fire cooking with Mediterranean herbs and California's finest produce.","photo":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/f2/Persea_americana_fruit_2.JPG/800px-Persea_americana_fruit_2.JPG"},
        {"name":"Tropisueno","price":35,"rating":4.2,"cuisine":"Cal-Med","tip":"The mezze board for two is an ideal starter before moving to the signature wood-grilled mains.","desc":"A SoMa bistro fusing California's abundant produce with bright Mediterranean spices, citrus vinaigrettes, and open-flame cooking techniques.","photo":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/3b/Home_made_sour_dough_bread.jpg/800px-Home_made_sour_dough_bread.jpg"},
        {"name":"Outerlands","price":36,"rating":4.6,"cuisine":"Cal-Med","tip":"The housemade Dutch pancake is a weekend brunch showstopper — come early to skip the wait.","desc":"A driftwood-clad Outer Sunset café and restaurant offering Cal-Med comfort dishes steps from Ocean Beach's misty shores.","photo":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/f2/Persea_americana_fruit_2.JPG/800px-Persea_americana_fruit_2.JPG"},
        {"name":"Mina Test Kitchen","price":68,"rating":4.7,"cuisine":"Cal-Med","tip":"This intimate tasting counter changes its menu monthly — check their site to preview before booking.","desc":"Michael Mina's experimental kitchen blending California ingredients with Mediterranean technique in ever-evolving tasting menus for curious diners.","photo":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/b4/Chez_Panisse_pizza.jpg/800px-Chez_Panisse_pizza.jpg"},
        {"name":"Octavia","price":55,"rating":4.7,"cuisine":"Cal-Med","tip":"The vegetable-forward tasting option is as satisfying as the omnivore menu — a rarity worth experiencing.","desc":"A Fillmore District gem led by Chef Melissa Perello, presenting refined Cal-Med plates rooted in farmers' market sourcing.","photo":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/94/Salad_platter.jpg/800px-Salad_platter.jpg"},
        {"name":"Cala","price":46,"rating":4.5,"cuisine":"Cal-Med","tip":"The wood-grilled octopus is the signature dish and a benchmark for the entire Cal-Med genre in SF.","desc":"A modern Mexican-Cal-Med hybrid restaurant in Hayes Valley led by Mexico City chef Gabriela Cámara using coastal California ingredients.","photo":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/b4/Chez_Panisse_pizza.jpg/800px-Chez_Panisse_pizza.jpg"},
        {"name":"Norcina","price":40,"rating":4.4,"cuisine":"Cal-Med","tip":"The house-cured charcuterie plate pairs beautifully with their small but well-chosen Italian wine list.","desc":"A NoPa neighborhood trattoria channeling central Italian mountain cooking through a California lens with thoughtful meat curing.","photo":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/3b/Home_made_sour_dough_bread.jpg/800px-Home_made_sour_dough_bread.jpg"},
        {"name":"Café Zoetrope","price":38,"rating":4.3,"cuisine":"Cal-Med","tip":"Dine on the piazza patio and ask about the Coppola wine pairings — they're reasonably priced and well chosen.","desc":"Francis Ford Coppola's North Beach café serving Italian-Cal-Med dishes inside a historic Sentinel Building with cinematic décor.","photo":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/94/Salad_platter.jpg/800px-Salad_platter.jpg"},
        {"name":"Barzotto","price":32,"rating":4.5,"cuisine":"Cal-Med","tip":"The cacio e pepe is made tableside on a large parmesan wheel during special evenings — ask in advance.","desc":"A Market Street pasta bar crafting California-inflected Italian classics with housemade noodles and seasonal vegetable preparations.","photo":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/f2/Persea_americana_fruit_2.JPG/800px-Persea_americana_fruit_2.JPG"},
        {"name":"Bi-Rite Creamery","price":7,"rating":4.8,"cuisine":"Ice Cream","tip":"The salted caramel with housemade waffle cone is the definitive order — don't overthink it.","desc":"A Mission District icon producing small-batch, organic ice cream with inventive flavors that draw lines stretching around the block.","photo":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/fc/Al._Wielkopolska_Poznan.jpg/960px-Al._Wielkopolska_Poznan.jpg"},
        {"name":"Humphry Slocombe","price":8,"rating":4.7,"cuisine":"Ice Cream","tip":"The Secret Breakfast — bourbon and cornflakes ice cream — is their signature and never disappoints.","desc":"A Mission and Ferry Building ice cream shop beloved for irreverent, inventive flavors that challenge and delight in equal measure.","photo":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/65/Anton_Faymann_055_Auto_Colour.jpg/960px-Anton_Faymann_055_Auto_Colour.jpg"},
        {"name":"Mitchell's Ice Cream","price":6,"rating":4.6,"cuisine":"Ice Cream","tip":"Try the ube or macapuno coconut — the Filipino-inspired flavors are what make Mitchell's truly unique in SF.","desc":"A family-run Noe Valley institution since 1953 specializing in tropical and Filipino-inspired ice cream flavors rarely found elsewhere.","photo":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/fc/Al._Wielkopolska_Poznan.jpg/960px-Al._Wielkopolska_Poznan.jpg"},
        {"name":"Smitten Ice Cream","price":9,"rating":4.7,"cuisine":"Ice Cream","tip":"Watch the liquid nitrogen process up close — it's theatrical and the texture it creates is genuinely exceptional.","desc":"A Cow Hollow creamery flash-freezing each scoop to order with liquid nitrogen for an ultra-creamy, never-icy consistency.","photo":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/84/A_counter_is_selling_ice_cream.jpg/960px-A_counter_is_selling_ice_cream.jpg"},
        {"name":"Garden Creamery","price":7,"rating":4.5,"cuisine":"Ice Cream","tip":"Their rotating seasonal sorbets are vegan-friendly and often more interesting than the dairy options.","desc":"A Mission and Outer Sunset shop crafting inventive ice cream and sorbet flavors inspired by the Bay Area's multicultural food scene.","photo":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/fc/Al._Wielkopolska_Poznan.jpg/960px-Al._Wielkopolska_Poznan.jpg"},
        {"name":"Gelato Classico","price":6,"rating":4.4,"cuisine":"Ice Cream","tip":"The pistachio and dark chocolate combination is a classic pairing that showcases their Italian gelato mastery.","desc":"A North Beach neighborhood gelato shop producing authentic Italian-style small-batch gelato using traditional techniques and imported ingredients.","photo":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/84/A_counter_is_selling_ice_cream.jpg/960px-A_counter_is_selling_ice_cream.jpg"},
        {"name":"Sweetheart Ice Cream","price":7,"rating":4.4,"cuisine":"Ice Cream","tip":"Try the Taiwanese shaved ice in summer — it's lighter than a scoop and packed with fresh fruit.","desc":"A Richmond District gem serving both scooped ice cream and Taiwanese-style shaved ice loaded with toppings and syrups.","photo":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/65/Anton_Faymann_055_Auto_Colour.jpg/960px-Anton_Faymann_055_Auto_Colour.jpg"},
        {"name":"Alegio Gelato","price":8,"rating":4.6,"cuisine":"Ice Cream","tip":"The single-origin chocolate gelato changes with each cacao harvest — ask the staff about the current bean's origin.","desc":"A Berkeley-born gelato artisan with SF locations focused on bean-to-bar chocolate gelatos and seasonal Italian flavor profiles.","photo":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/65/Anton_Faymann_055_Auto_Colour.jpg/960px-Anton_Faymann_055_Auto_Colour.jpg"},
        {"name":"Ice Cream Bar","price":9,"rating":4.5,"cuisine":"Ice Cream","tip":"Order a phosphate soda alongside your scoop — it's a nostalgic pairing that the soda fountain does beautifully.","desc":"A 1930s-style soda fountain in Cole Valley scooping housemade ice cream alongside retro phosphate sodas and sundaes.","photo":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/e/e1/-Korean_Icecream_-Tasty_-Family_time_-Yummy.jpg"},
        {"name":"Yank Sing","price":38,"rating":4.7,"cuisine":"Dim Sum","tip":"Come on a weekday to avoid weekend crowds and enjoy a more relaxed cart-service experience.","desc":"A Financial District institution renowned for its elevated, expertly prepared dim sum served from roving carts to business lunchers and families alike.","photo":"https://commons.wikimedia.org/w/resources/assets/file-type-icons/fileicon-ogg.png"},
        {"name":"Ton Kiang","price":28,"rating":4.6,"cuisine":"Dim Sum","tip":"The hakka-style stuffed tofu is a house specialty not found at most other Cantonese dim sum spots.","desc":"A Richmond District favorite offering Cantonese and Hakka dim sum with an impressive variety of har gow, siu mai, and regional specialties.","photo":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/94/Dim_sam.jpg/960px-Dim_sam.jpg"},
        {"name":"Dim Sum Club","price":30,"rating":4.5,"cuisine":"Dim Sum","tip":"Order the egg tarts fresh from the oven — ask your server when the next batch is coming out.","desc":"A SoMa dim sum restaurant bringing the bustling Cantonese teahouse tradition to the heart of San Francisco's tech corridor.","photo":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/5e/Healty_Food.jpg/960px-Healty_Food.jpg"},
        {"name":"Dragon Beaux","price":42,"rating":4.8,"cuisine":"Dim Sum","tip":"Make a reservation — this is one of the few SF dim sum spots that takes them and it fills fast.","desc":"An upscale Richmond District dim sum restaurant elevating classic Cantonese dumplings with premium ingredients and stunning presentations.","photo":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/5e/Healty_Food.jpg/960px-Healty_Food.jpg"},
        {"name":"Hong Kong Lounge II","price":29,"rating":4.6,"cuisine":"Dim Sum","tip":"The turnip cakes here are pan-fried to order rather than steamed — a crispier, richer version worth seeking out.","desc":"A Richmond District teahouse offering a deep menu of traditional Cantonese dim sum in a comfortable banquet-style setting.","photo":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/4c/Looking_up_at_The_Hive.JPG/960px-Looking_up_at_The_Hive.JPG"},
        {"name":"Koi Palace","price":35,"rating":4.7,"cuisine":"Dim Sum","tip":"Arrive at 10 AM sharp on weekends to minimize waits and get the full rotating cart selection.","desc":"A celebrated Daly City destination famous for live seafood tanks and some of the most skilled dim sum cooks in the Bay Area.","photo":"https://commons.wikimedia.org/w/resources/assets/file-type-icons/fileicon-ogg.png"},
        {"name":"City View Restaurant","price":26,"rating":4.5,"cuisine":"Dim Sum","tip":"Grab a number early and browse the Financial District streets while you wait — it's worth the patience.","desc":"A downtown Cantonese dim sum staple with old-school cart service and a devoted lunch crowd from the surrounding offices.","photo":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/94/Dim_sam.jpg/960px-Dim_sam.jpg"},
        {"name":"Palette Tea House","price":40,"rating":4.7,"cuisine":"Dim Sum","tip":"The colorful crystal dumplings are as beautiful as they are delicious — order the sampler to see them all.","desc":"An artful Ghirardelli Square dim sum restaurant known for vibrant, visually stunning dumplings that merge Cantonese craft with modern flair.","photo":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/94/Dim_sam.jpg/960px-Dim_sam.jpg"},
        {"name":"Good Mong Kok Bakery","price":8,"rating":4.5,"cuisine":"Dim Sum","tip":"Bring cash and point at what looks good — the turnover is fast and items are cheapest in the city.","desc":"A cash-only Chinatown counter selling freshly steamed bao, siu mai, and sticky rice at some of SF's lowest prices.","photo":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/94/Dim_sam.jpg/960px-Dim_sam.jpg"},
        {"name":"Golden Gate Bakery","price":5,"rating":4.8,"cuisine":"Dim Sum To-Go","tip":"The egg custard tarts sell out daily — arrive by 10 AM or expect to find the shutters closed.","desc":"A legendary Chinatown bakery with decades-long lines for its iconic, flaky-crust egg custard tarts warm from the oven.","photo":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/54/Dimsum.jpg/960px-Dimsum.jpg"},
        {"name":"Cheung Hing Chinese Restaurant","price":9,"rating":4.4,"cuisine":"Dim Sum To-Go","tip":"The char siu bao (BBQ pork buns) travel well — grab a bag for a picnic in Dolores Park.","desc":"A Sunset District takeout counter beloved for its freshly steamed and baked dim sum items at wallet-friendly prices.","photo":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/5e/Healty_Food.jpg/960px-Healty_Food.jpg"},
        {"name":"Wing Lee Bakery","price":6,"rating":4.3,"cuisine":"Dim Sum To-Go","tip":"Arrive early on weekends for the freshest sticky rice lotus leaf wraps straight from the steamer.","desc":"A Clement Street institution offering to-go dim sum classics, roast meats, and baked goods to the Richmond District neighborhood.","photo":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/4c/Looking_up_at_The_Hive.JPG/960px-Looking_up_at_The_Hive.JPG"},
        {"name":"Eastern Bakery","price":5,"rating":4.3,"cuisine":"Dim Sum To-Go","tip":"The moon cakes are available year-round here — a rare find outside of the Mid-Autumn Festival season.","desc":"San Francisco's oldest Chinatown bakery, operating since 1924 and still selling classic Chinese pastries and dim sum to-go items.","photo":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/54/Dimsum.jpg/960px-Dimsum.jpg"},
        {"name":"Dim Sum Corner","price":8,"rating":4.4,"cuisine":"Dim Sum To-Go","tip":"Order by the piece and mix freely — the taro dumplings and pineapple buns are particularly well made.","desc":"A compact Sunset takeout shop turning out freshly made dim sum bites in a grab-and-go format perfect for beach picnics.","photo":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/5e/Healty_Food.jpg/960px-Healty_Food.jpg"},
        {"name":"HK Gourmet Deli","price":7,"rating":4.3,"cuisine":"Dim Sum To-Go","tip":"The roasted duck paired with a pineapple bun makes for a surprisingly great improvised sandwich.","desc":"A Richmond District deli combining Cantonese roast meats with steamed dim sum to-go items in an efficient counter format.","photo":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/54/Dimsum.jpg/960px-Dimsum.jpg"},
        {"name":"New Tung Kee Noodle House","price":10,"rating":4.2,"cuisine":"Dim Sum To-Go","tip":"Call ahead on weekends to reserve a bag of fresh wontons — they sell fast for good reason.","desc":"A Chinatown noodle shop offering dim sum staples and hand-folded wontons as a popular takeaway option for locals.","photo":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/94/Dim_sam.jpg/960px-Dim_sam.jpg"},
        {"name":"Mama Ji's","price":12,"rating":4.5,"cuisine":"Dim Sum To-Go","tip":"The pan-fried pork potstickers come in generous quantities — ideal for a casual group picnic.","desc":"A Castro neighborhood kitchen preparing Northern Chinese dumplings and dim sum snacks fresh to order for takeout.","photo":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/5e/Healty_Food.jpg/960px-Healty_Food.jpg"},
        {"name":"Bao Bei Chinese Brasserie To-Go","price":13,"rating":4.5,"cuisine":"Dim Sum To-Go","tip":"The steamed soup dumplings pack cleanly for takeaway if you eat them within fifteen minutes of pickup.","desc":"A Chinatown brasserie with a robust takeout menu of modern Shanghainese dim sum favorites and small plates.","photo":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/5e/Healty_Food.jpg/960px-Healty_Food.jpg"},
        {"name":"Kin Khao","price":32,"rating":4.7,"cuisine":"Northern Thai","tip":"The khao soi is the must-order dish — a Northern Thai coconut curry noodle soup that rivals Chiang Mai originals.","desc":"A Michelin Bib Gourmand Thai restaurant in the Parc 55 Hotel presenting authentic Northern Thai cuisine rarely found outside Thailand.","photo":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/4a/LaoFood_LarbNeua.JPG/800px-LaoFood_LarbNeua.JPG"},
        {"name":"Farmhouse Kitchen Thai Cuisine","price":28,"rating":4.6,"cuisine":"Northern Thai","tip":"The crying tiger beef is a beloved house specialty — order it medium-rare for the best flavor.","desc":"A Mission and Oakland restaurant led by a Northern Thai family bringing heirloom recipes and vibrant market-sourced ingredients to SF.","photo":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/cf/Khao_Soi_Northern_Thai_food_%E0%B8%82%E0%B9%89%E0%B8%B2%E0%B8%A7%E0%B8%8B%E0%B8%AD%E0%B8%A2_%E0%B8%9C%E0%B8%B1%E0%B8%81%E0%B8%94%E0%B8%AD%E0%B8%87.jpg/800px-Khao_Soi_Northern_Thai_food_%E0%B8%82%E0%B9%89%E0%B8%B2%E0%B8%A7%E0%B8%8B%E0%B8%AD%E0%B8%A2_%E0%B8%9C%E0%B8%B1%E0%B8%81%E0%B8%94%E0%B8%AD%E0%B8%87.jpg"},
        {"name":"Marnee Thai","price":20,"rating":4.5,"cuisine":"Northern Thai","tip":"The predictive menu by the legendary owner is a SF institution — let him choose your dishes.","desc":"An Inner Sunset neighborhood gem run by an eccentric owner-chef famous for his accurate flavor recommendations and fragrant curries.","photo":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/85/0020-%E0%B8%A7%E0%B8%B1%E0%B8%94%E0%B8%9E%E0%B8%A3%E0%B8%B0%E0%B8%AA%E0%B8%B4%E0%B8%87%E0%B8%AB%E0%B9%8C%E0%B8%A7%E0%B8%A3%E0%B8%A1%E0%B8%AB%E0%B8%B2%E0%B8%A7%E0%B8%B4%E0%B8%AB%E0%B8%B2%E0%B8%A3.jpg/800px-0020-%E0%B8%A7%E0%B8%B1%E0%B8%94%E0%B8%9E%E0%B8%A3%E0%B8%B0%E0%B8%AA%E0%B8%B4%E0%B8%87%E0%B8%AB%E0%B9%8C%E0%B8%A7%E0%B8%A3%E0%B8%A1%E0%B8%AB%E0%B8%B2%E0%B8%A7%E0%B8%B4%E0%B8%AB%E0%B8%B2%E0%B8%A3.jpg"},
        {"name":"Songbird Thai Kitchen","price":25,"rating":4.4,"cuisine":"Northern Thai","tip":"Request extra khao niao (sticky rice) for dipping into the Northern Thai larb — it elevates the dish considerably.","desc":"A compact Tenderloin restaurant focusing on Northern Thai street food flavors with house-pounded herb pastes and fresh-milled spice blends.","photo":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/cf/Khao_Soi_Northern_Thai_food_%E0%B8%82%E0%B9%89%E0%B8%B2%E0%B8%A7%E0%B8%8B%E0%B8%AD%E0%B8%A2_%E0%B8%9C%E0%B8%B1%E0%B8%81%E0%B8%94%E0%B8%AD%E0%B8%87.jpg/800px-Khao_Soi_Northern_Thai_food_%E0%B8%82%E0%B9%89%E0%B8%B2%E0%B8%A7%E0%B8%8B%E0%B8%AD%E0%B8%A2_%E0%B8%9C%E0%B8%B1%E0%B8%81%E0%B8%94%E0%B8%AD%E0%B8%87.jpg"},
        {"name":"Zaap Thai","price":22,"rating":4.4,"cuisine":"Northern Thai","tip":"The sai oua Northern Thai sausage is a rare find in SF — order it as an appetizer.","desc":"A casual Thai restaurant in the Inner Richmond dedicated to Northern Thai recipes with complex spice profiles and fresh ingredients.","photo":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/cf/Khao_Soi_Northern_Thai_food_%E0%B8%82%E0%B9%89%E0%B8%B2%E0%B8%A7%E0%B8%8B%E0%B8%AD%E0%B8%A2_%E0%B8%9C%E0%B8%B1%E0%B8%81%E0%B8%94%E0%B8%AD%E0%B8%87.jpg/800px-Khao_Soi_Northern_Thai_food_%E0%B8%82%E0%B9%89%E0%B8%B2%E0%B8%A7%E0%B8%8B%E0%B8%AD%E0%B8%A2_%E0%B8%9C%E0%B8%B1%E0%B8%81%E0%B8%94%E0%B8%AD%E0%B8%87.jpg"},
        {"name":"Thai Idea Vegetarian","price":18,"rating":4.3,"cuisine":"Northern Thai","tip":"The mock-meat dishes are impressive — even committed carnivores often can't distinguish the satay from the real thing.","desc":"A Tenderloin Thai restaurant applying Northern Thai spicing techniques to a fully vegetarian menu with creative mock-meat options.","photo":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/cf/Nam_phrik_kapi_%28cropped%29.JPG/800px-Nam_phrik_kapi_%28cropped%29.JPG"},
        {"name":"Basil Thai Restaurant","price":24,"rating":4.4,"cuisine":"Northern Thai","tip":"The massaman curry is slow-cooked for hours — it's a warming choice on foggy SF evenings.","desc":"A SoMa Thai restaurant with a broad menu that includes several Northern Thai curry and noodle specialties alongside familiar Bangkok classics.","photo":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/85/0020-%E0%B8%A7%E0%B8%B1%E0%B8%94%E0%B8%9E%E0%B8%A3%E0%B8%B0%E0%B8%AA%E0%B8%B4%E0%B8%87%E0%B8%AB%E0%B9%8C%E0%B8%A7%E0%B8%A3%E0%B8%A1%E0%B8%AB%E0%B8%B2%E0%B8%A7%E0%B8%B4%E0%B8%AB%E0%B8%B2%E0%B8%A3.jpg/800px-0020-%E0%B8%A7%E0%B8%B1%E0%B8%94%E0%B8%9E%E0%B8%A3%E0%B8%B0%E0%B8%AA%E0%B8%B4%E0%B8%87%E0%B8%AB%E0%B9%8C%E0%B8%A7%E0%B8%A3%E0%B8%A1%E0%B8%AB%E0%B8%B2%E0%B8%A7%E0%B8%B4%E0%B8%AB%E0%B8%B2%E0%B8%A3.jpg"},
        {"name":"Hawker Fare","price":26,"rating":4.6,"cuisine":"Northern Thai","tip":"The whole fried fish with chili-lime dressing is a showpiece — bring a group to share it properly.","desc":"James Syhabout's Mission restaurant channeling the flavors of Northern Thailand and Laos through bold street-food dishes and natural wines.","photo":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/cf/Khao_Soi_Northern_Thai_food_%E0%B8%82%E0%B9%89%E0%B8%B2%E0%B8%A7%E0%B8%8B%E0%B8%AD%E0%B8%A2_%E0%B8%9C%E0%B8%B1%E0%B8%81%E0%B8%94%E0%B8%AD%E0%B8%87.jpg/800px-Khao_Soi_Northern_Thai_food_%E0%B8%82%E0%B9%89%E0%B8%B2%E0%B8%A7%E0%B8%8B%E0%B8%AD%E0%B8%A2_%E0%B8%9C%E0%B8%B1%E0%B8%81%E0%B8%94%E0%B8%AD%E0%B8%87.jpg"},
        {"name":"Lotus of Siam SF","price":29,"rating":4.5,"cuisine":"Northern Thai","tip":"The Northern Thai specialty set is the best way to sample multiple regional dishes in a single sitting.","desc":"A Bay Area spin on the celebrated Las Vegas Thai restaurant focusing on the distinctive flavors of Northern Thailand's Lanna cuisine.","photo":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/cf/Nam_phrik_kapi_%28cropped%29.JPG/800px-Nam_phrik_kapi_%28cropped%29.JPG"},
        {"name":"Liholiho Yacht Club","price":58,"rating":4.8,"cuisine":"Hawaiian-SF Fusion","tip":"The baked Hawaii dessert is a show-stopping tableside experience — always save room for it.","desc":"A Nob Hill sensation from chef Ravi Kapur blending Hawaiian comfort cooking with California seasonality in a festive, reservation-required dining room.","photo":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e8/Gobi_manchurian.jpg/800px-Gobi_manchurian.jpg"},
        {"name":"Poi Dog","price":16,"rating":4.5,"cuisine":"Hawaiian-SF Fusion","tip":"The plate lunch specials rotate daily — follow their social media to plan your visit around your favorite.","desc":"A Hayes Valley snack shop and catering operation bringing Hawaiian plate lunch culture to SF with local produce upgrades.","photo":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/69/Motherhood_and_apple_pie.jpg/800px-Motherhood_and_apple_pie.jpg"},
        {"name":"Bini's Kitchen","price":18,"rating":4.4,"cuisine":"Hawaiian-SF Fusion","tip":"The loco moco with grass-fed beef and gravy over brown rice is a heartier, more nutritious SF upgrade.","desc":"A Mission counter blending Hawaiian plate lunch traditions with California's health-conscious ingredient sourcing for a feel-good fusion experience.","photo":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e8/Gobi_manchurian.jpg/800px-Gobi_manchurian.jpg"},
        {"name":"Huli Huli Hawaiian BBQ","price":20,"rating":4.3,"cuisine":"Hawaiian-SF Fusion","tip":"The rotisserie chicken basted in huli huli sauce is worth the wait when it comes off the spit.","desc":"A casual Sunset District spot specializing in Hawaiian rotisserie chicken and plate lunches with a California freshness sensibility.","photo":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/69/Motherhood_and_apple_pie.jpg/800px-Motherhood_and_apple_pie.jpg"},
        {"name":"Mahalo","price":22,"rating":4.5,"cuisine":"Hawaiian-SF Fusion","tip":"The poke build-your-own bowl lets you explore flavor pairings that go well beyond standard tuna-soy-sesame.","desc":"A Castro poke and plate lunch bar incorporating Bay Area produce and Japanese pantry staples into Hawaiian bowl traditions.","photo":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e8/Gobi_manchurian.jpg/800px-Gobi_manchurian.jpg"},
        {"name":"Kahai Street Kitchen","price":17,"rating":4.4,"cuisine":"Hawaiian-SF Fusion","tip":"The spam musubi is available all day and is the ideal quick snack between neighborhood explorations.","desc":"A pop-up turned brick-and-mortar Hawaiian comfort food kitchen beloved for its garlic shrimp, musubi, and macaroni salad.","photo":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e8/Gobi_manchurian.jpg/800px-Gobi_manchurian.jpg"},
        {"name":"The Bird SF","price":14,"rating":4.4,"cuisine":"Hawaiian-SF Fusion","tip":"The garlic-aioli chicken sandwich with a side of mac salad is a perfect hybrid of SF and Hawaii.","desc":"A fast-casual SoMa spot known for its sandwich game, drawing on Hawaiian plate lunch flavors in a grab-and-go format.","photo":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e8/Gobi_manchurian.jpg/800px-Gobi_manchurian.jpg"},
        {"name":"Ono Hawaiian BBQ SF","price":16,"rating":4.2,"cuisine":"Hawaiian-SF Fusion","tip":"The combo plate with teriyaki beef and macaroni salad is the quintessential value order on the menu.","desc":"A chain with strong Bay Area roots faithfully replicating Hawaiian plate lunch culture for a loyal local following.","photo":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e8/Gobi_manchurian.jpg/800px-Gobi_manchurian.jpg"},
        {"name":"Kanak Attack","price":19,"rating":4.5,"cuisine":"Hawaiian-SF Fusion","tip":"The pineapple-glazed pork belly bowl is the signature fusion dish that best captures the Hawaiian-SF spirit.","desc":"A Mission District Hawaiian-SF fusion kitchen celebrating Pacific Islander food culture through locally sourced California ingredients and island techniques.","photo":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e8/Gobi_manchurian.jpg/800px-Gobi_manchurian.jpg"},
        {"name":"China Live","price":45,"rating":4.6,"cuisine":"Chinese-California","tip":"The market floor is worth browsing before your meal — the imported pantry items make excellent food gifts.","desc":"A Chinatown culinary marketplace and restaurant from chef George Chen merging premium Chinese culinary traditions with California market ingredients.","photo":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/0/0d/Collage_Chinese_Cuisine_by_User-EME.png/800px-Collage_Chinese_Cuisine_by_User-EME.png"},
        {"name":"Mister Jiu's","price":65,"rating":4.8,"cuisine":"Chinese-California","tip":"The whole roasted duck is a centerpiece dish — order it at least two days in advance.","desc":"A Michelin-starred Chinatown restaurant from chef Brandon Jew reinterpreting Chinese-American culinary history through a California farm-to-table lens.","photo":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/c2/Kung-pao-shanghai.jpg/800px-Kung-pao-shanghai.jpg"},
        {"name":"Palette Chinese","price":38,"rating":4.5,"cuisine":"Chinese-California","tip":"The soup dumplings filled with crab and pork broth are a standout fusion of Eastern technique and Western richness.","desc":"A modern SoMa restaurant blending Shanghainese technique with California seasonal produce for refined Chinese-California small plate dining.","photo":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/c2/Kung-pao-shanghai.jpg/800px-Kung-pao-shanghai.jpg"},
        {"name":"Eight Tables by George Chen","price":85,"rating":4.7,"cuisine":"Chinese-California","tip":"The prix-fixe tasting menu is the only option — surrender to the chef's vision for the full experience.","desc":"An intimate eight-table Chinatown dining room presenting a curated tasting menu of refined Chinese-California cuisine with imperial-era hospitality.","photo":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/ca/Flickr_preppybyday_4665999863--General_Tso%27s_Chicken.jpg/800px-Flickr_preppybyday_4665999863--General_Tso%27s_Chicken.jpg"},
        {"name":"Bao Bei Chinese Brasserie","price":36,"rating":4.6,"cuisine":"Chinese-California","tip":"The tea-smoked duck crepe is the definitive starter that sets the tone for the California-Chinese fusion to follow.","desc":"A chic Chinatown brasserie applying modern California restaurant sensibility to a menu inspired by Shanghai's Golden Age of dining.","photo":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/88/Chen_Mapo_Tofu.jpg/800px-Chen_Mapo_Tofu.jpg"},
        {"name":"Z & Y Restaurant","price":30,"rating":4.5,"cuisine":"Chinese-California","tip":"The Dungeness crab with Sichuan peppercorns is a SF original that fuses local shellfish with Chinese spice craft.","desc":"A Chinatown Sichuan restaurant that has pioneered Chinese-California fusion by pairing local Bay Area seafood with authentic Sichuan preparations.","photo":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/95/Charsiu.jpg/800px-Charsiu.jpg"},
        {"name":"Wok Wiz Chinatown Tour Dinner","price":28,"rating":4.3,"cuisine":"Chinese-California","tip":"Book a table on a weekday to get the full cooking demonstration without the weekend tourist crowds.","desc":"A Chinatown dining experience blending cultural storytelling with California-influenced Chinese home cooking in an educational and welcoming setting.","photo":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/ca/Flickr_preppybyday_4665999863--General_Tso%27s_Chicken.jpg/800px-Flickr_preppybyday_4665999863--General_Tso%27s_Chicken.jpg"},
        {"name":"Mission Chinese Food","price":32,"rating":4.6,"cuisine":"Chinese-California","tip":"The salt-cod fried rice is one of the most discussed dishes in SF Chinese-California cooking — order it first.","desc":"Danny Bowien's influential Mission restaurant remixing Sichuan Chinese cooking through a California counterculture lens with bold, playful flavor.","photo":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/88/Chen_Mapo_Tofu.jpg/800px-Chen_Mapo_Tofu.jpg"},
        {"name":"House of Nanking","price":22,"rating":4.4,"cuisine":"Chinese-California","tip":"Let the owner order for you — he's opinionated and reliably steers you toward the best dishes.","desc":"A legendary Chinatown institution where the chef-owner improvises dishes based on your preferences using California produce and Chinese technique.","photo":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/88/Chen_Mapo_Tofu.jpg/800px-Chen_Mapo_Tofu.jpg"},
        {"name":"The Kebab Shop SF","price":14,"rating":4.4,"cuisine":"Greek Fast Casual","tip":"The spicy harissa sauce is made in-house and can be added to any bowl or pita — always say yes.","desc":"A fast-casual Greek and Mediterranean counter turning out hand-carved doner kebabs and fresh falafel wraps at lunchtime speed.","photo":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/0/01/Grk2020.jpg/800px-Grk2020.jpg"},
        {"name":"Souvla","price":18,"rating":4.7,"cuisine":"Greek Fast Casual","tip":"The Greek frozen yogurt with honey and walnuts is the ideal finish — don't skip dessert here.","desc":"A Hayes Valley Greek fast-casual restaurant roasting premium meats on a vertical spit and serving them in warm pita with tzatziki.","photo":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/a8/MussakasMeMelitsanesKePatates01.JPG/800px-MussakasMeMelitsanesKePatates01.JPG"},
        {"name":"Oren's Hummus","price":16,"rating":4.5,"cuisine":"Greek Fast Casual","tip":"Order the hummus with warm chickpeas and olive oil drizzle — the simplest preparation is the most revealing.","desc":"A Mountain View–born Israeli-Greek hummus bar with an SF outpost serving silky, freshly blended hummus bowls with warm pita.","photo":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e8/Souvlaki_in_Athens.JPG/800px-Souvlaki_in_Athens.JPG"},
        {"name":"Gyros by the Embarcadero","price":13,"rating":4.2,"cuisine":"Greek Fast Casual","tip":"Eat outdoors along the waterfront — it's the most satisfying way to enjoy a gyro in San Francisco.","desc":"A quick-serve Embarcadero counter offering classic pork and chicken gyros, spanakopita, and fresh Greek salads with bay views.","photo":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e8/Souvlaki_in_Athens.JPG/800px-Souvlaki_in_Athens.JPG"},
        {"name":"Nikos Taverna SF","price":20,"rating":4.4,"cuisine":"Greek Fast Casual","tip":"The loukoumades (Greek honey doughnuts) sell out early in the day — ask if they're still available when you arrive.","desc":"A casual Sunset District Greek counter serving fast-paced Mediterranean classics with generous portions and a friendly neighborhood vibe.","photo":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/a8/MussakasMeMelitsanesKePatates01.JPG/800px-MussakasMeMelitsanesKePatates01.JPG"},
        {"name":"Athens Pita","price":12,"rating":4.3,"cuisine":"Greek Fast Casual","tip":"Customize your pita with extra kalamata olives and roasted red peppers for a more robust Mediterranean flavor profile.","desc":"A budget-friendly Richmond District counter wrapping grilled proteins, fresh vegetables, and house-made tzatziki in hand-pressed pita.","photo":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e8/Souvlaki_in_Athens.JPG/800px-Souvlaki_in_Athens.JPG"},
        {"name":"Zante's Indian Pizzeria","price":17,"rating":4.2,"cuisine":"Greek Fast Casual","tip":"The gyro pizza mashup is an SF original worth trying even if it sounds unusual — it works remarkably well.","desc":"A Mission District institution experimenting with Mediterranean flavors on pizza dough, including a beloved gyro-topped pie that locals adore.","photo":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/0/01/Grk2020.jpg/800px-Grk2020.jpg"},
        {"name":"Falafel Drive-In SF","price":10,"rating":4.4,"cuisine":"Greek Fast Casual","tip":"The falafel pita with tahini, pickled turnips, and hot sauce is the definitive order — keep it classic.","desc":"A no-frills counter serving some of SF's crispiest falafel wraps, beloved by the lunch crowd for speed and quality.","photo":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/37/Spanakopita.jpg/800px-Spanakopita.jpg"},
        {"name":"Kronos Greek Grill","price":15,"rating":4.3,"cuisine":"Greek Fast Casual","tip":"The avgolemono soup is a comforting starter on cold foggy SF afternoons — always worth ordering.","desc":"A Financial District Greek fast-casual spot serving gyros, souvlaki skewers, and Mediterranean bowls to the downtown lunch crowd.","photo":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/37/Spanakopita.jpg/800px-Spanakopita.jpg"},
        {"name":"Zazie","price":28,"rating":4.7,"cuisine":"California Brunch","tip":"Sit in the garden patio on sunny weekends — it's one of SF's most charming outdoor brunch settings.","desc":"A Cole Valley French-California bistro with a devoted brunch following for its lemon ricotta pancakes and garden courtyard.","photo":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/c6/Kells_Street_Kitchen_cheeseburger_Romford_outdoor_market_at_Market_Place_Romford_London_02.jpg/960px-Kells_Street_Kitchen_cheeseburger_Romford_outdoor_market_at_Market_Place_Romford_London_02.jpg"},
        {"name":"Plow Restaurant","price":26,"rating":4.6,"cuisine":"California Brunch","tip":"Arrive by 8:30 AM to beat the Potrero Hill brunch queue that forms quickly after 9.","desc":"A beloved Potrero Hill brunch institution known for buttery lemon ricotta pancakes and perfectly cooked California farm eggs.","photo":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/c6/Kells_Street_Kitchen_cheeseburger_Romford_outdoor_market_at_Market_Place_Romford_London_02.jpg/960px-Kells_Street_Kitchen_cheeseburger_Romford_outdoor_market_at_Market_Place_Romford_London_02.jpg"},
        {"name":"Brenda's French Soul Food","price":24,"rating":4.7,"cuisine":"California Brunch","tip":"The beignets with dipping sauces arrive hot — eat them immediately while the powdered sugar is still warm.","desc":"A Tenderloin institution fusing New Orleans French Creole cooking with California brunch sensibility via outstanding beignets and eggs Sardou.","photo":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/aa/Chips_with_ham_and_egg_at_Epping_Essex%2C_England.jpg/960px-Chips_with_ham_and_egg_at_Epping_Essex%2C_England.jpg"},
        {"name":"Nopa Brunch","price":35,"rating":4.7,"cuisine":"California Brunch","tip":"The wood-fired brunch items are only available on weekends — plan your visit accordingly for the best menu.","desc":"The weekend brunch version of the beloved NoPa dinner spot, serving California seasonal brunch dishes around the wood-fired hearth.","photo":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/10/King_prawn_starter_at_the_White_Hart_Inn%2C_Moreton%2C_Essex%2C_England.jpg/960px-King_prawn_starter_at_the_White_Hart_Inn%2C_Moreton%2C_Essex%2C_England.jpg"},
        {"name":"Réveille Coffee Co.","price":18,"rating":4.5,"cuisine":"California Brunch","tip":"The avocado toast on their house sourdough is textbook California brunch done with genuinely good ingredients.","desc":"A North Beach and Castro café serving California-style brunch plates alongside expertly pulled espresso drinks in a sunny setting.","photo":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/30/Cheese_salad_roll_at_The_Original_Tea_Hut_at_High_Beach%2C_Essex%2C_England_01_lower_dynamic_range.jpg/960px-Cheese_salad_roll_at_The_Original_Tea_Hut_at_High_Beach%2C_Essex%2C_England_01_lower_dynamic_range.jpg"},
        {"name":"Bix Restaurant Sunday Brunch","price":40,"rating":4.6,"cuisine":"California Brunch","tip":"Request a jazz brunch reservation — the live music and art deco interior make it a full SF experience.","desc":"A glamorous 1930s supper club in Jackson Square reviving California brunch elegance with craft cocktails and Dungeness crab omelets.","photo":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/10/King_prawn_starter_at_the_White_Hart_Inn%2C_Moreton%2C_Essex%2C_England.jpg/960px-King_prawn_starter_at_the_White_Hart_Inn%2C_Moreton%2C_Essex%2C_England.jpg"},
        {"name":"Marla Bakery","price":22,"rating":4.5,"cuisine":"California Brunch","tip":"The breakfast flatbread changes with the season — it's always the most creative thing on the menu.","desc":"An Inner Richmond wood-fire bakery and café crafting California brunch dishes around a live-fire hearth with exceptional pastry foundations.","photo":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/fa/Seafood_linguine_at_the_White_Hart_Inn%2C_Moreton%2C_Essex%2C_England_-_Fujifilm_Superia_200_emulation.jpg/960px-Seafood_linguine_at_the_White_Hart_Inn%2C_Moreton%2C_Essex%2C_England_-_Fujifilm_Superia_200_emulation.jpg"},
        {"name":"Tartine Manufactory Brunch","price":30,"rating":4.8,"cuisine":"California Brunch","tip":"Order the grain bowl alongside a pastry — the combination of savory and sweet brunch dishes is the right call.","desc":"The expanded Mission bakery-restaurant from Chad Robertson serving ambitious California brunch plates built around their celebrated fermented grains.","photo":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/ac/20110703-24-brunch_spread_%285974097802%29.jpg/960px-20110703-24-brunch_spread_%285974097802%29.jpg"},
        {"name":"Stable Café","price":20,"rating":4.4,"cuisine":"California Brunch","tip":"The outdoor courtyard in the historic carriage house is a hidden gem for weekend brunch — book it specifically.","desc":"A Mission café inside a restored 1907 stable building serving California brunch plates with a locavore sourcing ethos.","photo":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/30/Cheese_salad_roll_at_The_Original_Tea_Hut_at_High_Beach%2C_Essex%2C_England_01_lower_dynamic_range.jpg/960px-Cheese_salad_roll_at_The_Original_Tea_Hut_at_High_Beach%2C_Essex%2C_England_01_lower_dynamic_range.jpg"},
        {"name":"Dumpling Story","price":18,"rating":4.6,"cuisine":"Pan-Asian Dumplings","tip":"The Hong Shao Rou steamed bun with braised pork belly is the showpiece — order it first.","desc":"A Richmond District pan-Asian dumpling shop crafting hand-folded dumplings across Chinese, Japanese, and Korean dumpling traditions in one menu.","photo":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/88/%E5%8F%B0%E7%81%A3%E5%8D%97%E6%8A%95%E8%8D%89%E5%B1%AF%E6%B0%B4%E9%A4%83Nantou%2C_Taiwan_Caotun_dumplings.jpg/800px-%E5%8F%B0%E7%81%A3%E5%8D%97%E6%8A%95%E8%8D%89%E5%B1%AF%E6%B0%B4%E9%A4%83Nantou%2C_Taiwan_Caotun_dumplings.jpg"},
        {"name":"Dumpling Kitchen","price":16,"rating":4.5,"cuisine":"Pan-Asian Dumplings","tip":"The pan-fried pork and chive dumplings come out crispy-bottomed — order them over the steamed version for texture.","desc":"A Sunset District dumpling house producing handmade Northern Chinese jiaozi and soup dumplings at accessible prices for large groups.","photo":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/3a/A_Xiaolongbao_from_The_Modern_Shanghai.jpg/800px-A_Xiaolongbao_from_The_Modern_Shanghai.jpg"},
        {"name":"Wo Hing General Store","price":22,"rating":4.5,"cuisine":"Pan-Asian Dumplings","tip":"The mapo tofu dumplings are a creative fusion that showcases how the kitchen pushes beyond traditional forms.","desc":"A Mission restaurant and bar serving inventive pan-Asian dumplings inspired by diaspora Chinese cooking and California ingredient availability.","photo":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/40/HK_SYP_%E8%A5%BF%E7%87%9F%E7%9B%A4_Sai_Ying_Pun_Kwan_Yick_Building_%E5%90%8D%E6%98%9F%E6%B5%B7%E9%AE%AE%E9%85%92%E5%AE%B6_Star_Seafood_Restaurant_food_%E5%90%9E%E9%BA%B5_Wonton_dim_sum_October_2020_SS2_01.jpg/800px-HK_SYP_%E8%A5%BF%E7%87%9F%E7%9B%A4_Sai_Ying_Pun_Kwan_Yick_Building_%E5%90%8D%E6%98%9F%E6%B5%B7%E9%AE%AE%E9%85%92%E5%AE%B6_Star_Seafood_Restaurant_food_%E5%90%9E%E9%BA%B5_Wonton_dim_sum_October_2020_SS2_01.jpg"},
        {"name":"Gyoza Bar","price":20,"rating":4.5,"cuisine":"Pan-Asian Dumplings","tip":"The truffle and Parmesan gyoza is a SF-inflected fusion specialty that shouldn't work but absolutely does.","desc":"A Japantown-adjacent bar and kitchen specializing in creative Japanese gyoza with fillings that draw on both Asian and California pantries.","photo":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/3a/A_Xiaolongbao_from_The_Modern_Shanghai.jpg/800px-A_Xiaolongbao_from_The_Modern_Shanghai.jpg"},
        {"name":"Dumpling Time","price":25,"rating":4.7,"cuisine":"Pan-Asian Dumplings","tip":"The XLB soup dumplings require technique — the staff will instruct first-timers on the proper bite-and-sip method.","desc":"A SoMa dumpling restaurant with a theatrical open kitchen producing Instagram-famous soup dumplings, har gow, and Japanese-style shu mai.","photo":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/3a/A_Xiaolongbao_from_The_Modern_Shanghai.jpg/800px-A_Xiaolongbao_from_The_Modern_Shanghai.jpg"},
        {"name":"Kingdom of Dumpling","price":14,"rating":4.4,"cuisine":"Pan-Asian Dumplings","tip":"The lamb and scallion dumplings are a Northern Chinese specialty not commonly found elsewhere in SF.","desc":"A Sunset District counter beloved for its generous, wallet-friendly portions of handmade dumplings across multiple regional Chinese styles.","photo":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/88/%E5%8F%B0%E7%81%A3%E5%8D%97%E6%8A%95%E8%8D%89%E5%B1%AF%E6%B0%B4%E9%A4%83Nantou%2C_Taiwan_Caotun_dumplings.jpg/800px-%E5%8F%B0%E7%81%A3%E5%8D%97%E6%8A%95%E8%8D%89%E5%B1%AF%E6%B0%B4%E9%A4%83Nantou%2C_Taiwan_Caotun_dumplings.jpg"},
        {"name":"Momo SF","price":19,"rating":4.4,"cuisine":"Pan-Asian Dumplings","tip":"The Nepalese momo with tomato achaar is a distinct style from the Chinese dumplings nearby — try both.","desc":"A Tenderloin restaurant specializing in Nepalese steamed and fried momos alongside Tibetan and South Asian dumpling traditions.","photo":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/3a/A_Xiaolongbao_from_The_Modern_Shanghai.jpg/800px-A_Xiaolongbao_from_The_Modern_Shanghai.jpg"},
        {"name":"Bun Mee","price":15,"rating":4.3,"cuisine":"Pan-Asian Dumplings","tip":"Pair a Vietnamese-style bahn mi with the steamed bao for a broad taste of pan-Asian bread and dumpling traditions.","desc":"A Hayes Valley and Marina shop fusing Vietnamese bánh mì culture with Japanese steamed bao in a casual grab-and-go format.","photo":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/f4/Baozi_Chengdu.JPG/800px-Baozi_Chengdu.JPG"},
        {"name":"Kusakabe","price":35,"rating":4.6,"cuisine":"Pan-Asian Dumplings","tip":"The gyoza flight comparing three regional styles is available at the bar counter — ask about it specifically.","desc":"A Financial District omakase restaurant that incorporates refined dumpling courses alongside sushi in a cross-cultural pan-Asian tasting format.","photo":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/40/HK_SYP_%E8%A5%BF%E7%87%9F%E7%9B%A4_Sai_Ying_Pun_Kwan_Yick_Building_%E5%90%8D%E6%98%9F%E6%B5%B7%E9%AE%AE%E9%85%92%E5%AE%B6_Star_Seafood_Restaurant_food_%E5%90%9E%E9%BA%B5_Wonton_dim_sum_October_2020_SS2_01.jpg/800px-HK_SYP_%E8%A5%BF%E7%87%9F%E7%9B%A4_Sai_Ying_Pun_Kwan_Yick_Building_%E5%90%8D%E6%98%9F%E6%B5%B7%E9%AE%AE%E9%85%92%E5%AE%B6_Star_Seafood_Restaurant_food_%E5%90%9E%E9%BA%B5_Wonton_dim_sum_October_2020_SS2_01.jpg"},
        {"name":"Brenda's Meat & Three","price":26,"rating":4.7,"cuisine":"French Creole Brunch","tip":"The crawfish étouffée over grits is the brunch dish that most faithfully captures New Orleans on a SF morning.","desc":"Brenda Buenviaje's second SF restaurant diving deeper into Southern soul food and Louisiana French Creole brunch classics.","photo":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/37/Ratatouille_home_cooked.jpg/800px-Ratatouille_home_cooked.jpg"},
        {"name":"Boxing Room","price":32,"rating":4.6,"cuisine":"French Creole Brunch","tip":"The Cajun bloody mary with pickled okra is the essential brunch cocktail — it sets the Louisiana mood immediately.","desc":"A Hayes Valley Louisiana Creole brunch and dinner destination serving gumbo, po'boys, and beignets with California ingredient sensibility.","photo":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/5a/Soupe_%C3%A0_l%27oignon.jpg/800px-Soupe_%C3%A0_l%27oignon.jpg"},
        {"name":"Bon Marché Brasserie","price":38,"rating":4.5,"cuisine":"French Creole Brunch","tip":"The pain perdu (French toast) made with brioche is a weekend-only item — plan specifically to try it.","desc":"A Union Square brasserie blending Parisian French café tradition with New Orleans Creole brunch flavors in a polished setting.","photo":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/5a/Gourmet_coq_au_vin.jpg/800px-Gourmet_coq_au_vin.jpg"},
        {"name":"1300 on Fillmore","price":35,"rating":4.6,"cuisine":"French Creole Brunch","tip":"The shrimp and grits is prepared with California cream and local shrimp — a regional take worth ordering.","desc":"A Fillmore District jazz-age supper club celebrating Harlem Renaissance culture through Southern French Creole brunch dishes and live music.","photo":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/2a/Croissant-Petr_Kratochvil.jpg/800px-Croissant-Petr_Kratochvil.jpg"},
        {"name":"Old Skool Café","price":22,"rating":4.4,"cuisine":"French Creole Brunch","tip":"Reserve a dinner-as-brunch slot on Friday nights when the full Creole menu and live jazz are both available.","desc":"A Bayview community supper club run by at-risk youth serving Southern French Creole dishes in a jazz supper-club setting.","photo":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/29/Beef_bourguignon_NYT.jpg/800px-Beef_bourguignon_NYT.jpg"},
        {"name":"Le Colonial","price":42,"rating":4.5,"cuisine":"French Creole Brunch","tip":"The French-Vietnamese fusion brunch is best experienced on the upstairs lounge level with its colonial plantation décor.","desc":"A Union Square restaurant evoking French colonial Indochina through a Vietnamese-French fusion brunch menu in an opulent tropical setting.","photo":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/37/Ratatouille_home_cooked.jpg/800px-Ratatouille_home_cooked.jpg"},
        {"name":"Café de la Presse","price":28,"rating":4.3,"cuisine":"French Creole Brunch","tip":"The croque madame with a glass of rosé at 11 AM is a quintessential Parisian-SF brunch indulgence.","desc":"A Union Square French brasserie and European newsstand serving classic Creole-French brunch dishes in a lively corner café atmosphere.","photo":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/29/Beef_bourguignon_NYT.jpg/800px-Beef_bourguignon_NYT.jpg"},
        {"name":"Mayes Oyster House","price":36,"rating":4.4,"cuisine":"French Creole Brunch","tip":"The oyster po'boy brunch special is only available on Sundays — it's a Creole-Californian landmark dish.","desc":"A Polk Street historic oyster bar channeling French-Creole brunch tradition through raw bar presentations and Louisiana-inspired egg dishes.","photo":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/17/2014_0531_Cr%C3%A8me_br%C3%BBl%C3%A9e_Doi_Mae_Salong_%28cropped%29.jpg/800px-2014_0531_Cr%C3%A8me_br%C3%BBl%C3%A9e_Doi_Mae_Salong_%28cropped%29.jpg"},
        {"name":"Chez Maman West","price":24,"rating":4.5,"cuisine":"French Creole Brunch","tip":"The crepes with beurre noisette and sea salt are a simple, perfect expression of French Creole brunch craft.","desc":"A cozy Potrero Hill French bistro serving rustic Provençal and Creole brunch dishes in an intimate neighborhood setting.","photo":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/6a/Jacques_Lameloise%2C_escab%C3%A8che_d%27%C3%A9crevisses_sur_gaspacho_d%27asperge_et_cresson.jpg/800px-Jacques_Lameloise%2C_escab%C3%A8che_d%27%C3%A9crevisses_sur_gaspacho_d%27asperge_et_cresson.jpg"}
